knowledge_graph.title: Hot dog
knowledge_graph.description: A hot dog is a dish consisting of a grilled, steamed, or boiled sausage served in the slit of a partially sliced bun. The term hot dog can refer to the sausage itself. The sausage used is a wiener or a frankfurter. The names of these sausages commonly refer to their assembled dish.

related_questions.question: Why is it called hotdog?
related_questions.snippet: References to dachshund sausages and ultimately hot dogs can be traced to German immigrants in the 1800s. These immigrants brought not only sausages to America, but dachshund dogs. The name most likely began as a joke about the Germans' small, long, thin dogs.

related_questions.question: Is hot dog healthy?
related_questions.snippet: While hot dogs are a favorite staple for many summertime festivities, they may not be suitable for certain people and can negatively affect health when consumed in excess. Hot dogs tend to be high in sodium, and high sodium intake has been linked to an increased risk of heart disease and high blood pressure.

related_questions.snippet: What are hot dogs made of? Hot dogs are made from the emulsified meat trimmings of chicken, beef, or pork. This meat mixture is blended with other ingredients (like preservatives, spices, and coloring) into a batter-like substance.
